{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:romans.12",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "romans",
    "chapterNumber": 12,
    "referenceLabel": "Romans 12",
    "summary": "Source text for Romans 12 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:1",
      "text": "I appeal to you therefore, brethren, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to God, which is your spiritual worship.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:2",
      "text": "Do not be conformed to this world but be transformed by the renewal of your mind, that you may prove what is the will of God, what is good and acceptable and perfect.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:3",
      "text": "For by the grace given to me I bid every one among you not to think of himself more highly than he ought to think, but to think with sober judgment, each according to the measure of faith which God has assigned him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:4",
      "text": "For as in one body we have many members, and all the members do not have the same function,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:5",
      "text": "so we, though many, are one body in Christ, and individually members one of another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:6",
      "text": "Having gifts that differ according to the grace given to us, let us use them: if prophecy, in proportion to our faith;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:7",
      "text": "if service, in our serving; he who teaches, in his teaching;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:8",
      "text": "he who exhorts, in his exhortation; he who contributes, in liberality; he who gives aid, with zeal; he who does acts of mercy, with cheerfulness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:9",
      "text": "Let love be genuine; hate what is evil, hold fast to what is good;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:10",
      "text": "love one another with brotherly affection; outdo one another in showing honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:11",
      "text": "Never flag in zeal, be aglow with the Spirit, serve the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:12",
      "text": "Rejoice in your hope, be patient in tribulation, be constant in prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:13",
      "text": "Contribute to the needs of the saints, practice hospitality.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:14",
      "text": "Bless those who persecute you; bless and do not curse them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:15",
      "text": "Rejoice with those who rejoice, weep with those who weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:16",
      "text": "Live in harmony with one another; do not be haughty, but associate with the lowly; never be conceited.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:17",
      "text": "Repay no one evil for evil, but take thought for what is noble in the sight of all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:18",
      "text": "If possible, so far as it depends upon you, live peaceably with all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:19",
      "text": "Beloved, never avenge yourselves, but leave it to the wrath of God; for it is written, “Vengeance is mine, I will repay, says the Lord.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:20",
      "text": "No, “if your enemy is hungry, feed him; if he is thirsty, give him drink; for by so doing you will heap burning coals upon his head.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:romans.12.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "romans",
      "chapterNumber": 12,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Romans 12:21",
      "text": "Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
